jobs.prompt:
Build `Code&DBs/Workflow/surfaces/app/src/dashboard/OperatingModelEditor.tsx`.

This is the PRIMARY editing surface for operating models — NOT a pipeline with step cards. It's a document-style text editor where the prose IS the spec.

The component renders:

1. **Title bar**: Editable workflow name, status badge (DRAFT/COMPILING/LIVE), [Commit] amber button

2. **Prose editor area**: A contenteditable div (or textarea with overlay) where the compiled prose lives. @references render as `<span class='om-ref om-ref--integration'>@gmail/inbox</span>`, #references as `<span class='om-ref om-ref--object'>#contact/email</span>`, {variables} as `<span class='om-ref om-ref--variable'>{priority}</span>`, agent names as `<span class='om-ref om-ref--agent'>triage-agent</span>`. Clicking any reference calls `onReferenceClick(ref)`.

3. **Unresolved references section**: If any refs are unresolved, show a yellow warning box listing them with 'Configure' links

4. **Execution section** (at bottom): Shows `lastRun`, `processedToday`, `recentRuns` from props. Green/red dots with timestamps.

Props interface:
```typescript
interface OperatingModelEditorProps {
  workflowId?: string;
  initialProse?: string;
  compiledProse?: string;
  references?: Reference[];
  unresolved?: string[];
  executionData?: {
    processedToday: number;
    recentRuns: Array<{id: string; status: string; ago: string; label: string}>;
    lastRunAgo?: string;
    triggerDescription?: string;
  };
  compileStatus?: 'idle' | 'compiling' | 'compiled' | 'error';
  onProseChange?: (prose: string) => void;
  onReferenceClick?: (ref: Reference) => void;
  onCommit?: (prose: string) => void;
  onBack?: () => void;
}

interface Reference {
  id: string;
  type: 'integration' | 'object' | 'variable' | 'agent';
  slug: string;
  span?: [number, number];
  config?: Record<string, unknown>;
  resolved?: boolean;
}
```

The prose rendering: take `compiledProse` (a string) and replace reference patterns with colored spans. Use a simple regex pass — no contenteditable complexity. Use a `<pre style={{whiteSpace: 'pre-wrap'}}>` or a div with dangerouslySetInnerHTML (sanitized — only replace known patterns).

When the prose textarea changes (onBlur), call `onProseChange` with the new raw text.

Style everything with CSS classes (no inline styles except layout). Add CSS to `Code&DBs/Workflow/surfaces/app/src/dashboard/dashboard.css` at the end:
- `.om-editor` — full-height document editor container
- `.om-editor__prose` — large readable text area, Inter font, 18px, line-height 1.8, padding 32px
- `.om-ref` — inline badge, no border-radius on text, slight background tint
- `.om-ref--integration` — amber tint `rgba(245,166,35,0.15)`, amber text
- `.om-ref--object` — blue tint `rgba(88,166,255,0.15)`, blue text  
- `.om-ref--variable` — green tint `rgba(63,185,80,0.15)`, green text
- `.om-ref--agent` — purple tint `rgba(188,100,255,0.15)`, purple text
- `.om-execution` — execution panel at bottom, border-top, padding 24px
- `.om-run-item` — each recent run line with status dot

Import React only. No other dependencies. The file must compile cleanly with TypeScript.
